casebody.data:
PEOPLE of the State of Michigan, Plaintiff-Appellee,
v.
Nathan Phillip ASHBURN, Defendant-Appellant. SC: 157927
COA: 344170 Supreme Court of Michigan. June 20, 2018

Order

On order of the Chief Justice, the stipulation signed by counsel for the parties agreeing to the dismissal of this application for leave to appeal is considered, and the application for leave to appeal is DISMISSED with prejudice. The motion for immediate consideration of the application is denied as moot.
